          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Brandon</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 07-26-98 02:27 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I'm curious to find out what dispensers other people have found at garage sales, thrift stores and flea markets, and how much they were. I've found a non footed whistle and three 3.9 light blue batman dispensers for under $2. Please reply if you have a story you want to share!</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Rob</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 07-27-98 12:31 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Hello!<br>
            no garage sale luck for me, but ya know, I'm not too sure what to look for. I've looked around at the flea market with no luck...Should i be checking the booths that sell toys, or the booths that sell junk from the basement? I would think that both would not know the value of a dispenser, but a day at the flea market left me empty handed. Any tips for finding treasures at these places?</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>brien ZEP nyc</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 07-27-98 05:49 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I almost always see someone selling current PEZ for around $5.00 to $10.00. Personally I get my currents from the local .99 cent store!</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Alex</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 07-28-98 12:09 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">i love flea markets ...my finds include a mickey C ($7), Captian (Paul Revere) ($30!!), Raven ($20), Goofy A ($20), and a whole bunch of fat-eared bunnies, DrSkull A's, 3-pc witches, Pumpkin A's, etc ...but i get really pissed at all the people trying to sell current stuff for anywhere up to $30... for stuff like flintstones?? ..that's just riduculous... later gators</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Pimpbot3k</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 07-28-98 05:54 AM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">I have gotten alot of thrift store finds. A wonder woman with a raised star and a chick in egg on a green stem, no feet, and a purple egg. So just hang in there if you haven't found anything yet, something will come along</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
