            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">On sunday, I went to a antique show up here and for $15 i got:<br>
            Angel<br>
            Old Dr. Skull<br>
            Fat-Eared Bunny<br>
            Mowgali<br>
            Old Speedy Gonzales</font>
            <p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">That's pretty kewl, it works out to $2.50 a piece</font></p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>melissa</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 10-20-98 04:10 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">My best find was at a flea market, some guy had a bunch of 3.9 pez and i asked if he had any others, so i went to the flea market next month (it was only once a month) and i got a nurse in great shape for $10..the guy was like "i gotta make a couple bucks, so how about ten dollars?" i walked away happy, but he also had a doctor missing a few pieces, and i went back to buy that too, but he had sold it..</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
          <td width="18%" valign="top"><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>pezhead</b></font></td>
          <td>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><font size="1" color="#000080" face="Verdana, Arial">posted 10-22-98 04:09 PM CT (US)</font></font>
            <hr>
            <font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">We had three good finds. A Zorro was given to us for free when we found it a box of old toys that were being packed for a move. We also found a Mr. Ugly green face no feet at a garage sale for 10 cents. Our third find was a old Pluto with movable ears and no feet at a garage sale for 5 cents.</font>
          </td>
        </tr>
